### 1. Create a User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "labaaaa",
  "email": "laaabaaaa@g.com",
  "password": "123"
}

### 2. Get All Users
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users

### 3. Create an Apartment
POST http://localhost:8080/api/apartments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": "123 Baker Street, London"
}

### 4. Get All Apartments
GET http://localhost:8080/api/apartments

### 5. Add User to Apartment (Linking)
# Replace '1' with actual IDs from the previous GET requests
POST http://localhost:8080/api/apartments/1/members/1

### 6. Create an Expense
# user_id 1 pays for apartment_id 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "apartmentId": 1,
  "title": "Monthly Electricity",
  "category": "Utilities",
  "amount": 85.50,
  "expenseDate": "2026-01-10"
}

### 7. Create another Expense (Groceries)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId":1,
  "apartmentId": "1",
  "title": "Rum",
  "category": "Food",
  "amount": 120.00,
  "expenseDate": ""
}

### 8. Get All Expenses for an Apartment
GET http://localhost:8080/api/expenses/apartment/1

### 9. Update an Expense
# Change amount or category
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/expenses/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "apartmentId": 1,
  "title": "Monthly Electricity - Adjusted",
  "category": "Utilities",
  "amount": 90.00,
  "expenseDate": "2026-01-10"
}

### 10. Delete an Expense
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/expenses/1

### 11. Delete an Apartment
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/apartments/1